brokerProfiles.companyOverview:
Founded in 1994, First Choice Business Brokers has accelerated to become one of the largest Business Sales Organizations in the United States. Our team of business brokers come from diverse backgrounds in accounting, legal, banking, real estate, and insurance. Every broker has undergone rigorous initial training, supplemented by ongoing education, making First Choice brokers some of the most seasoned experts in business valuation, marketing, and negotiations. This wealth of knowledge and expertise consistently delivers excellent outcomes for both buyers and sellers.
The buying or selling of a business should never be compared to the purchasing or selling of a home. You deserve experienced, licensed professionals who specialize in business sales – you need First Choice Business Brokers. Our nationwide network of seasoned business sales professionals combines national reach with local market expertise. We offer buyers the greatest selection of businesses available and we provide Sellers with the personalized, confidential attention they deserve.
brokerProfiles.introduction:
With 28+ years in the mortgage industry and over $1B in closed loans, I specialize in helping clients navigate complex lending scenarios—especially self-employed borrowers and business owners with unique financials. I've worked as a loan officer, branch manager, and business owner, and I bring clarity, strategy, and personal service to every transaction.
I have deep experience working with small business owners and self-employed clients, understanding the intricate nuances of tax returns, income documentation, and the creative structuring often needed to get deals done. Whether it's analyzing K-1s, navigating write-offs, or leveraging bank statement programs, I know how to present your full financial picture in the best light.
Out of the office, I’ve spent 18 years as the head football coach at Scituate High School, winning 3 state championships (2018, 2021, 2024) and helping 100+ players reach college programs. Leadership and results drive everything I do—whether in the business world or on the sidelines. I've also started and continue to run Scituate Flag Football for the past 12 years.  We currently serve multiple communities on the South Shore.
Based in Scituate, MA with my wife Kelly (my college sweetheart) and our six amazing kids — five daughters and one son.

brokerProfiles.introduction:
Major New England based business brokerage firm with two divisions "Main Street" and "Middle Market" serving the Northeast including Metro New York. Four brokers and other cooperating brokers. Twenty years of experience in representing Buyers and Sellers.  Major markets are Boston, Rhode Island, Worcester, New Bedford, Metro New York, and Hartford.  

United Brokers Group LLC maintains a middle market brokerage division for transactions with values of $1 million or higher.  Unique focus on selling Northeast businesses to Buyers from outside this region.  Our brokers hold real estate licenses in multiple New England states and actively co-broke with licensed professionals who operate in compliance with the relevant state law. 

Leading generator of SBA loans with referral agreements with multiple banks. 

Specializing in manufacturing, insulation installation, healthcare, child day care, large gas stations and other closely held businesses. 

Contributing author and under contract with BizBuySell.

Marketing tactics include our enewsletter netowork, targeted decision maker direct mail from our numerous industry data bases, selected professional peer co-brokering, and internet marketing.

Many states regulate business brokerage.  We recommend that you work with licensed and bonded Business Brokers in compliance with relevant state law.  Rhode Island, for example, regulates business brokerage via  Rhode Island General Law 42-14-12 and please make sure any non-Rhode Island business broker you interview is in compliance with state law.  

The company maintains a large database of buyers and sellers segmented by industry type and state.  We aggressively, professionally, and confidentially market to this community of Buyers and Sellers.

The firm works with Buyers and Sellers to identify, evaluate, and select the best marketing strategies for their objectives and then professionally manages the process using contact management systems and a major data base.

United Brokers Group LLC specializes in supporting exit planning strategies.  We have buyers for many different types of businesses.  

The company works with properly credentialed third party business valuation experts such as those affiliated with Boston Valuation Services www.BostonValuations.com and www.ManhattanValuations.com who provide third party valuations for Buyers, Sellers, attorneys and lenders.  We generally limit valuations to only those provided by one of the five SBA Qualified Source categories such as a CPA with a ABV or CVA  designation.   Mr. Flynn is an "Industry Expert" to the Business Reference Guide in the manufacturing and staffing industry segments.  The Business Reference Guide is the leading provider of "Rules of Thumb" for business valuations and is published annually.

We are members of Rhode Island MLS, the National Association of Realtors, and also members of Kent-Washington Board of Realtors. Robert Flynn is an Associate Broker member of North Star Realty in the  Rhode Island office.

Mr. Flynn is a Cooperating Intermediary with the Gottesman Company in Manhattan and active in Metro New York, Worcester, Plymouth, Massachusetts, Hartford, New Bedford, and Boston.

Robert Flynn is also an author at www.Axial.net with various published articles. Please see archives in the "News and Articles" section of the www.unitedbrokersgrp.com website.

brokerProfiles.companyOverview:
CABOT Business Brokers is an established business brokerage firm representing buyers and sellers throughout the New England region.  Our staff is comprised of experienced business people who have owned and managed businesses themselves and are both knowledgeable and qualified to value and  market businesses, to identify appropriate potential acquirers, and to structure and close the business transaction.    
Our professional brokers work confidentially with sellers in valuing   their businesses, in preparing an effective marketing plan, and in negotiation and closing successful business sales.
With buyers we similarly approach and evaluate acquisition opportunities as disciplined business executives, reviewing not only business profitability and performance, but also valuing commensurate business strategy, the market and competitive environment, growth opportunities, and ROI.
If you are just beginning to consider selling your business, or are entertaining thoughts about a business acquisition, contact CABOT Business Brokers for a no-commitment, free consultation to explore how we might be able to provide you with valuable, competent assistance in this important decision.
brokerProfiles.introduction:
CABOT BUSINESS BROKERS - Professional, Experienced and Discrete in Valuing, Marketing and Selling Businesses.  As an accomplished entrepreneur and marketer, Bob has served as president/CEO of multiple successful businesses including start-up divisions of Johnson & Johnson, Cadbury Schweppes, Millipore, and a series of smaller, privately held and financed ventures. With an impressive success rate leading business start-ups and turn-arounds, Bob founded CABOT Business Brokers  as an outgrowth of his prior work with early-stage ventures and his identification of their need for a disciplined, experienced business approach when pursuing a sales transaction.
Bob holds both a BS in Mechanical Engineering and an MBA from Northeastern University.  He has taught entrepreneurial business courses at Manhattanville College and Quincy Junior College and is a member of the New England Business Brokers Association (NEBBA.) and is a licensed RE Salesperson in Massachusetts.
brokerProfiles.affiliations:
New England Business Brokers Assoc. (NEBBA)
BS Mechanical Engineering
MBA
brokerProfiles.services:
CABOT BUSINESS BROKERS Services include:
- We provide business valuations to reflect the true fair market value of your business.
- We confidentially market businesses through our own database of buyers, the internet, our network of brokers and industry experts, trade publications, newspapers and other sources.
- We assist business owners in preparing their business for sale.
- We interview, screen, and qualify prospective buyers.
- We assist the owner in negotiating offers, and tenaciously manage and resolve those unique issues and contingencies that may arise.
And CABOT carries out this whole process and is paid only upon the successful completion of the sale. Find out more about our services at www.cabotbb.com. 
If you are considering selling your business and want to better understand the sales process and how this would make sense for you now or in the future, please feel free to give us a call at 781.749.3087. As experienced business people and prior business owners ourselves, we at CABOT are pleased to assist and look forward to hearing from you.
brokerProfiles.tagline: Discrete, Professional and Experienced in Valuing, Marketing and Selling Businesses
